    "Figure 7: Metrics comparison between the four recommenders and the empirically observed data.",
    "Simulation initialized on real graph (white area) and on synthetic graph (grey area, see Section 6.7), the error bars in the latter case correspond to the standard deviations over 10 repetitions, starting from the same synthetic inputs 6.3 Within the population, the overexposure to negativity is extremely diverse, as depicted in Figure 8, with some users experiencing an overexposure of more than 300%.",
